328 class Control
329 {
330 public:
331 Edu totalDur{};
332 Evpu totalWidth{};
333 Evpu minWidth{};
334 Evpu allotWidth{};
335
336 static const xml::XmlElementArray<Control>& xmlMappingArray();
337 };
338
339 // Populated only when the XML node includes a <control> element
340 std::shared_ptr<Control> control;
341
342 // Populated for standard beat entries (inci > 0)
343 Edu dur{};
344 Evpu pos{};
345 Evpu endPos{};
346 Evpu minPos{};
347
348 void integrityCheck() override
349 {
350 OthersBase::integrityCheck();
351 if (control && getInci() != 0) {
352 MUSX_INTEGRITY_ERROR("Beat chart for measure " + std::to_string(getCmper()) + " has a control instance in inci " + std::to_string(*getInci()));
353 }
354 if (getInci() == 0 && !control) {
355 control = std::make_shared<Control>();
356 MUSX_INTEGRITY_ERROR("Beat chart for measure " + std::to_string(getCmper()) + " is missing its control instance.");
357 }
358 }
359
360 constexpr static std::string_view XmlNodeName = "beatChart";
361 static const xml::XmlElementArray<BeatChartElement>& xmlMappingArray();
362};

508class FontDefinition : public OthersBase
509{
510 static constexpr uint32_t SYMBOL_CHARSET_MAC = 0xfff; // (4095)
511 static constexpr uint32_t SYMBOL_CHARSET_WIN = 2;
512
513public:
515 explicit FontDefinition(const DocumentWeakPtr& document, Cmper partId, ShareMode shareMode, Cmper cmper)
516 : OthersBase(document, partId, shareMode, cmper) {}
517
520 enum class CharacterSetBank
521 {
522 MacOS,
523 Windows
524 };
525
526 // Public properties corresponding to the XML structure
527 CharacterSetBank charsetBank{};
528 int charsetVal{};
533 int pitch{};
534 int family{};
535 std::string name;
536
550 bool calcIsSymbolFont() const
551 {
552 if (charsetBank == CharacterSetBank::MacOS && charsetVal == SYMBOL_CHARSET_MAC) {
553 return true;
554 }
555 if (charsetBank == CharacterSetBank::Windows && charsetVal == SYMBOL_CHARSET_WIN) {
556 return true;
557 }
558 return false;
559 }
560
561 constexpr static std::string_view XmlNodeName = "fontName";
562 static const xml::XmlElementArray<FontDefinition>& xmlMappingArray();
563};

576class Frame : public OthersBase
577{
578public:
580 explicit Frame(const DocumentWeakPtr& document, Cmper partId, ShareMode shareMode, Cmper cmper, Inci inci = 0)
581 : OthersBase(document, partId, shareMode, cmper, inci) {}
582
583 // Public properties corresponding to the XML structure
584 EntryNumber startEntry{};
585 EntryNumber endEntry{};
586 Edu startTime{};
587
590 void iterateRawEntries(std::function<bool(const std::shared_ptr<Entry>& entry)> iterator) const;
591
596 std::vector<std::shared_ptr<const Entry>> getEntries() const;
597
598 void integrityCheck() override
599 {
600 this->OthersBase::integrityCheck();
601 if (startTime && (startEntry || endEntry)) {
602 MUSX_INTEGRITY_ERROR("Frame " + std::to_string(getCmper()) + " has non-zero startTime and non-zero startEntry or endEntry.");
603 }
604 if (!startTime && !startEntry) {
605 MUSX_INTEGRITY_ERROR("Frame " + std::to_string(getCmper()) + " has no start entry.");
606 }
607 if (!startTime && !endEntry) {
608 MUSX_INTEGRITY_ERROR("Frame " + std::to_string(getCmper()) + " has no end entry.");
609 }
610 }
611
612 constexpr static std::string_view XmlNodeName = "frameSpec";
613 static const xml::XmlElementArray<Frame>& xmlMappingArray();
614};

2213 void integrityCheck() override
2214 {
2215 OthersBase::integrityCheck();
2216 if (!staffLines && !customStaff) {
2217 MUSX_INTEGRITY_ERROR("Staff or StaffStyle " + std::to_string(getCmper()) + " has neither a standard nor a custom staff definition.");
2218 } else if (staffLines && customStaff) {
2219 MUSX_INTEGRITY_ERROR("Staff or StaffStyle " + std::to_string(getCmper()) + " has both a standard and a custom staff definition.");
2220 }
2221 if (customStaff) { // guarantee ascending order of staves.
2222 std::sort(customStaff.value().begin(), customStaff.value().end(),
2223 [](const auto& a, const auto& b) { return a < b; });
2224 }
2225 if (transposition) {
2226 if (!transposition->chromatic && !transposition->keysig) {
2227 MUSX_INTEGRITY_ERROR("Staff or StaffStyle " + std::to_string(getCmper()) + " has transposition with neither keysig nor chromatic transposition defined.");
2228 } else if (transposition->chromatic && transposition->keysig) {
2229 MUSX_INTEGRITY_ERROR("Staff or StaffStyle " + std::to_string(getCmper()) + " has transposition with both keysig and chromatic transposition defined.");
2230 }
2231 }
2232 if (useNoteFont && !noteFont) {
2233 noteFont = std::make_shared<FontInfo>(getDocument()); // do this first to avoid unreachable code warning, since MUSX_INTEGRITY_ERROR might throw
2234 MUSX_INTEGRITY_ERROR("Staff or StaffStyle " + std::to_string(getCmper()) + " specifies to use a custom notehead font, but no custom font was provided.");
2235 }
2236 }
2237
2238 bool requireAllFields() const override { return false; }
